10#ifndef EIGEN_CXX11_FIXED_POINT_MAT_VEC_PRODUCT_H
11#define EIGEN_CXX11_FIXED_POINT_MAT_VEC_PRODUCT_H

14namespace Eigen {
15namespace internal {
16
17// Mat-Vec product
18// Both lhs and rhs are encoded as 8bit signed integers
19template<typename Index, typename LhsMapper, bool ConjugateLhs, typename RhsMapper, bool ConjugateRhs, int Version>
20struct general_matrix_vector_product<Index,QInt8,LhsMapper,ColMajor,ConjugateLhs,QInt8,RhsMapper,ConjugateRhs,Version>
21{
22EIGEN_DONT_INLINE static void run(
23 Index rows, Index cols,
24 const LhsMapper& lhs,
25 const RhsMapper& rhs,
26 QInt32* res, Index resIncr,
27 QInt8 alpha);
28};
29
30template<typename Index, typename LhsMapper, bool ConjugateLhs, typename RhsMapper, bool ConjugateRhs, int Version>
31EIGEN_DONT_INLINE void general_matrix_vector_product<Index,QInt8,LhsMapper,ColMajor,ConjugateLhs,QInt8,RhsMapper,ConjugateRhs,Version>::run(
32 Index rows, Index cols,
33 const LhsMapper& lhs,
34 const RhsMapper& rhs,
35 QInt32* res, Index resIncr,
36 QInt8 alpha)
37{
38 eigen_assert(alpha.value == 1);
39 eigen_assert(resIncr == 1);
40 eigen_assert(rows > 0);
41 eigen_assert(cols > 0);
42
43 for (Index i = 0; i < rows; ++i) {
44 for (Index j = 0; j < cols; ++j) {
45 res[i] += lhs(i, j) * rhs(j, 0);
46 }
47 }
48}
49
50
51// Mat-Vec product
52// The lhs is encoded using 8bit signed integers, the rhs using 8bit unsigned integers
53template<typename Index, typename LhsMapper, bool ConjugateLhs, typename RhsMapper, bool ConjugateRhs, int Version>
54struct general_matrix_vector_product<Index,QInt8,LhsMapper,ColMajor,ConjugateLhs,QUInt8,RhsMapper,ConjugateRhs,Version>
55{
56EIGEN_DONT_INLINE static void run(
57 Index rows, Index cols,
58 const LhsMapper& lhs,
59 const RhsMapper& rhs,
60 QInt32* res, Index resIncr,
61 QUInt8 alpha);
62};
63
64template<typename Index, typename LhsMapper, bool ConjugateLhs, typename RhsMapper, bool ConjugateRhs, int Version>
65EIGEN_DONT_INLINE void general_matrix_vector_product<Index,QInt8,LhsMapper,ColMajor,ConjugateLhs,QUInt8,RhsMapper,ConjugateRhs,Version>::run(
66 Index rows, Index cols,
67 const LhsMapper& lhs,
68 const RhsMapper& rhs,
69 QInt32* res, Index resIncr,
70 QUInt8 alpha)
71{
72 eigen_assert(alpha.value == 1);
73 eigen_assert(resIncr == 1);
74 eigen_assert(rows > 0);
75 eigen_assert(cols > 0);
76
77 for (Index i = 0; i < rows; ++i) {
78 for (Index j = 0; j < cols; ++j) {
79 res[i] += lhs(i, j) * rhs(j, 0);
80 }
81 }
82}

85// Mat-Vec product
86// The lhs is encoded using bit unsigned integers, the rhs using 8bit signed integers
87template<typename Index, typename LhsMapper, bool ConjugateLhs, typename RhsMapper, bool ConjugateRhs, int Version>
88struct general_matrix_vector_product<Index,QUInt8,LhsMapper,ColMajor,ConjugateLhs,QInt8,RhsMapper,ConjugateRhs,Version>
89{
90EIGEN_DONT_INLINE static void run(
91 Index rows, Index cols,
92 const LhsMapper& lhs,
93 const RhsMapper& rhs,
94 QInt32* res, Index resIncr,
95 QInt8 alpha);
96};

98template<typename Index, typename LhsMapper, bool ConjugateLhs, typename RhsMapper, bool ConjugateRhs, int Version>
99EIGEN_DONT_INLINE void general_matrix_vector_product<Index,QUInt8,LhsMapper,ColMajor,ConjugateLhs,QInt8,RhsMapper,ConjugateRhs,Version>::run(
100 Index rows, Index cols,
101 const LhsMapper& lhs,
102 const RhsMapper& rhs,
103 QInt32* res, Index resIncr,
104 QInt8 alpha)
105{
106 eigen_assert(alpha.value == 1);
107 eigen_assert(resIncr == 1);
108 eigen_assert(rows > 0);
109 eigen_assert(cols > 0);
110
111 for (Index i = 0; i < rows; ++i) {
112 for (Index j = 0; j < cols; ++j) {
113 res[i] += lhs(i, j) * rhs(j, 0);
114 }
115 }
116}
